  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA244-kiḷavi">iḵtaṟattoṭu nilai valitta tōḻiyait talaivi mukampukkatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how SHE sought the favour of the confidante who was intent of standing up with virtue (~revealing the truth).</p>
        </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA244">
<l>            viḻunta mārip peruntaṇ cāraṟ</l>
<l>            kūtirk kūtaḷat talari nāṟu</l>
<l>            mātar vaṇṭi ṉayavarun tīṅkuraṉ</l>
<l>            maṇanāṟu cilampi ṉacuṇa mōrkku</l>
<l>            muyarmalai nāṭaṟ kuraitta loṉṟō </l>
<l>            tuyarmaruṅ kaṟiya vaṉṉaik kinnōy</l>
<l>            taṇiyumā ṟituveṉa vuraitta loṉṟō</l>
<l>            ceyyā yātaliṟ koṭiyai tōḻi</l>
<l>            maṇikeḻu neṭuvarai yaṇipeṟa nivanta</l>
<l>            ceyalai yantaḷi raṉṉaveṉ </l>
<l>            mataṉiṉ māmaip pacalaiyuṅ kaṇṭē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>As for telling one thing to the man from the land of high mountains,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the Acuṇam<note place="foot">The <term xml:lang="ta">Acuṇam</term> is another of these fabulous beasts. According to T.V.G., it is very fond of music and can be killed by a harsh tone. We find it in NA 304 and AN 88, which means there seems to be no old commentary passage explaining.</note> on the mountain-side fragrant with scents listens</l>
<l rend="indent2">to the desire-evoking<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">nayavarum</term>: another <term xml:lang="ta">peyareccam</term> does not seem to make sense here. We cannot but read it as an attribute.</note> sweet voice of the beautiful bees,</l>
<l rend="indent3">when the flowers of the Kūṭalam emit fragrance in the cool season</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the big cool slope in the shower that came down<note place="foot">Why <term xml:lang="ta">vīḻnta māri</term> and not <term xml:lang="ta">māri vīḻnta</term>?</note>,</l>
<l>as for telling one thing,</l>
<l rend="indent4">“this is the way to decrease this pain,”</l>
<l rend="indent4">to mother so that she may know of [my] misery</l>
<l>– because you don’t do it you [are] cruel, friend,</l>
<l>having seen the pallor of [my] dark complexion too, my strength failing,</l>
<l rend="indent2">as the pretty Aśoka sprouts</l>
<l rend="indent2">come up for the long mountain to be decorated, having sapphires.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
